1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a signal detection technique for massive MIMO systems, which involves processing and decoding of information signals. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the use of massive MIMO systems in heterogeneous networks, which involves network architecture and design. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a mathematical signal model for massive MIMO systems, which involves system modeling and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the separation of uplink signals for different user classes, which may involve multimedia data transmission. 
5. cs.COM (Computational Complexity): The paper presents a computational cost study for the proposed signal detection algorithm, which involves analyzing the complexity of the algorithm.
